H0.text: What is the common name of the clavicle. Collarbone

H1.text: What is the common name of the clavicle. Shoulderbone

H2.text: What is the common name of the clavicle. Armbridge

H3.text: What is the common name of the clavicle. Clavacle

A4.text: The clavicle, collarbone, or keybone is a slender, S-shaped long bone approximately 6 inches (15 cm) long that serves as a strut between the shoulder blade and the sternum (breastbone).
